pluginDNA.description: This plugin for IntelliJ IDEA and Android Studio enables you to develop Kotlin Multiplatform applications targeting Android, iOS, desktop, web, and server. Write business logic and UI once, and run your app on all supported platforms. Run, debug, and test applications on both iOS and Android directly from the IDE. Create a new multiplatform project in just a few clicks within the IDE. Preflight checks help you configure your environment, so everythings ready to go. Get basic Swift support in the IDE, including navigation, quick documentation, and cross-language debugging tools. More about Kotlin Multiplatform For IntelliJ, this plugin is now available on macOS, Windows, and Linux. Note: Due to system restrictions, the iOS target has limitations and still requires macOS. Android Studio support will follow.
